[
  {
    "text": "How many of you are tired",
    "start": 13.435,
    "duration": 2.691
  },
  {
    "text": "of seeing celebrities adopting kids\nfrom the African continent?",
    "start": 16.674,
    "duration": 4.461
  },
  {
    "text": "(Laughter)",
    "start": 21.159,
    "duration": 1.579
  },
  {
    "text": "Well, it's not all that bad.",
    "start": 24.342,
    "duration": 2.354
  },
  {
    "text": "I was adopted.",
    "start": 28.573,
    "duration": 1.368
  },
  {
    "text": "I grew up in rural Uganda,",
    "start": 31.451,
    "duration": 2.702
  },
  {
    "text": "lost both my parents\nwhen I was very, very young.",
    "start": 35.495,
    "duration": 2.768
  },
  {
    "text": "And when my parents passed,",
    "start": 39.978,
    "duration": 1.719
  },
  {
    "text": "I experienced all the negative\neffects of poverty,",
    "start": 42.467,
    "duration": 6.141
  },
  {
    "text": "from homelessness,",
    "start": 49.36,
    "duration": 1.619
  },
  {
    "text": "eating out of trash piles,",
    "start": 51.003,
    "duration": 1.769
  },
  {
    "text": "you name it.",
    "start": 53.539,
    "duration": 1.15
  },
  {
    "text": "But my life changed",
    "start": 56.603,
    "duration": 1.474
  },
  {
    "text": "when I got accepted into an orphanage.",
    "start": 59.038,
    "duration": 3.813
  },
  {
    "text": "Through one of those\nsponsor-an-orphan programs,",
    "start": 63.808,
    "duration": 2.347
  },
  {
    "text": "I was sponsored and given an opportunity\nto acquire an education.",
    "start": 66.924,
    "duration": 3.707
  },
  {
    "text": "I started off in Uganda.",
    "start": 71.963,
    "duration": 2.11
  },
  {
    "text": "I went through school, and the way\nthis particular program worked,",
    "start": 74.097,
    "duration": 3.754
  },
  {
    "text": "you finished high school\nand after high school,",
    "start": 77.875,
    "duration": 2.208
  },
  {
    "text": "you go learn a trade --\nto become a carpenter, a mechanic",
    "start": 80.107,
    "duration": 3.66
  },
  {
    "text": "or something along those lines.",
    "start": 83.791,
    "duration": 1.8
  },
  {
    "text": "My case was a little different.",
    "start": 86.559,
    "duration": 2.868
  },
  {
    "text": "The sponsor family that was sending\nthese 25 dollars a month",
    "start": 90.308,
    "duration": 4.093
  },
  {
    "text": "to this orphanage to sponsor me,",
    "start": 94.425,
    "duration": 2.412
  },
  {
    "text": "which -- I had never met them --",
    "start": 96.861,
    "duration": 1.852
  },
  {
    "text": "said, \"Well ...",
    "start": 99.702,
    "duration": 1.835
  },
  {
    "text": "we would like to send you\nto college instead.\"",
    "start": 102.813,
    "duration": 2.606
  },
  {
    "text": "Oh -- it gets better.",
    "start": 106.538,
    "duration": 1.228
  },
  {
    "text": "(Laughter)",
    "start": 107.79,
    "duration": 1.043
  },
  {
    "text": "And they said, \"If you get the paperwork,",
    "start": 108.857,
    "duration": 2.836
  },
  {
    "text": "we'll send you to school\nin America instead.\"",
    "start": 111.717,
    "duration": 2.903
  },
  {
    "text": "So with their help,",
    "start": 116.856,
    "duration": 1.587
  },
  {
    "text": "I went to the embassy\nand applied for the visa.",
    "start": 119.287,
    "duration": 3.296
  },
  {
    "text": "I got the visa.",
    "start": 123.216,
    "duration": 1.389
  },
  {
    "text": "I remember this day like it was yesterday.",
    "start": 124.629,
    "duration": 4.031
  },
  {
    "text": "I walked out of the embassy\nwith this piece of paper in my hand,",
    "start": 129.054,
    "duration": 3.364
  },
  {
    "text": "a hop in my step,",
    "start": 132.442,
    "duration": 1.715
  },
  {
    "text": "smile on my face,",
    "start": 134.181,
    "duration": 1.701
  },
  {
    "text": "knowing that my life is about to change.",
    "start": 135.906,
    "duration": 3.387
  },
  {
    "text": "I went home that night,",
    "start": 140.875,
    "duration": 1.59
  },
  {
    "text": "and I slept with my passport,",
    "start": 143.168,
    "duration": 1.814
  },
  {
    "text": "because I was afraid\nthat someone might steal it.",
    "start": 145.006,
    "duration": 2.307
  },
  {
    "text": "(Laughter)",
    "start": 147.337,
    "duration": 1.855
  },
  {
    "text": "I couldn't fall asleep.",
    "start": 149.216,
    "duration": 1.42
  },
  {
    "text": "I kept feeling it.",
    "start": 151.446,
    "duration": 1.318
  },
  {
    "text": "I had a good idea for security.",
    "start": 153.896,
    "duration": 1.829
  },
  {
    "text": "I was like, \"OK, I'm going\nto put it in a plastic bag,",
    "start": 156.324,
    "duration": 2.569
  },
  {
    "text": "and take it outside and dig a hole,\nand put it in there.\"",
    "start": 158.917,
    "duration": 3.507
  },
  {
    "text": "I did that, went back in the house.",
    "start": 163.706,
    "duration": 1.945
  },
  {
    "text": "I could not fall asleep. I was like,\n\"Maybe someone saw me.\"",
    "start": 165.675,
    "duration": 2.953
  },
  {
    "text": "I went back --",
    "start": 168.652,
    "duration": 1.151
  },
  {
    "text": "(Laughter)",
    "start": 169.827,
    "duration": 1.01
  },
  {
    "text": "I pulled it out, and I put it\nwith me the entire night --",
    "start": 170.861,
    "duration": 2.774
  },
  {
    "text": "all to say that it was\nan anxiety-filled night.",
    "start": 173.659,
    "duration": 2.958
  },
  {
    "text": "(Laughter)",
    "start": 176.641,
    "duration": 1.15
  },
  {
    "text": "Going to the US was,\njust like another speaker said,",
    "start": 178.203,
    "duration": 4.051
  },
  {
    "text": "was my first time to see a plane,",
    "start": 182.278,
    "duration": 2.354
  },
  {
    "text": "be on one, let alone sit on it\nto fly to another country.",
    "start": 184.656,
    "duration": 3.361
  },
  {
    "text": "December 15, 2006.",
    "start": 189.172,
    "duration": 2.509
  },
  {
    "text": "7:08pm.",
    "start": 192.061,
    "duration": 1.89
  },
  {
    "text": "I sat in seat 7A.",
    "start": 194.58,
    "duration": 2.969
  },
  {
    "text": "Fly Emirates.",
    "start": 198.009,
    "duration": 1.343
  },
  {
    "text": "One of the most gorgeous,\nbeautiful women I've ever seen walked up,",
    "start": 201.427,
    "duration": 3.678
  },
  {
    "text": "red little hat with a white veil.",
    "start": 206.246,
    "duration": 2.806
  },
  {
    "text": "I'm looking terrified,\nI have no idea what I'm doing.",
    "start": 209.792,
    "duration": 2.933
  },
  {
    "text": "She hands me this warm towel --",
    "start": 213.391,
    "duration": 2.226
  },
  {
    "text": "warm, steamy, snow white.",
    "start": 215.641,
    "duration": 2.081
  },
  {
    "text": "I'm looking at this warm towel;",
    "start": 219.686,
    "duration": 2.314
  },
  {
    "text": "I don't know what to do with my life,\nlet alone with this damn towel --",
    "start": 222.024,
    "duration": 3.394
  },
  {
    "text": "(Laughter)",
    "start": 225.442,
    "duration": 1.877
  },
  {
    "text": "(Applause)",
    "start": 227.343,
    "duration": 2.818
  },
  {
    "text": "I did one of the --",
    "start": 231.712,
    "duration": 1.339
  },
  {
    "text": "you know, anything anyone\ncould do in that situation:",
    "start": 233.075,
    "duration": 2.49
  },
  {
    "text": "look around, see what\neveryone else is doing.",
    "start": 236.043,
    "duration": 2.697
  },
  {
    "text": "I did the same.",
    "start": 238.764,
    "duration": 1.184
  },
  {
    "text": "Mind you, I drove about seven hours\nfrom my village to the airport that day.",
    "start": 240.549,
    "duration": 5.037
  },
  {
    "text": "So I grab this warm towel,",
    "start": 246.524,
    "duration": 2.05
  },
  {
    "text": "wipe my face just like\neveryone else is doing,",
    "start": 248.598,
    "duration": 3.145
  },
  {
    "text": "I look at it --",
    "start": 251.767,
    "duration": 1.446
  },
  {
    "text": "damn.",
    "start": 253.237,
    "duration": 1.165
  },
  {
    "text": "(Laughter)",
    "start": 254.426,
    "duration": 1.492
  },
  {
    "text": "It was all dirt brown.",
    "start": 256.983,
    "duration": 1.838
  },
  {
    "text": "(Laughter)",
    "start": 258.845,
    "duration": 1.15
  },
  {
    "text": "I remember being so embarrassed\nthat when she came by to pick it up,",
    "start": 260.94,
    "duration": 5.255
  },
  {
    "text": "I didn't give mine.",
    "start": 266.219,
    "duration": 1.227
  },
  {
    "text": "(Laughter)",
    "start": 267.47,
    "duration": 1.117
  },
  {
    "text": "I still have it.",
    "start": 268.611,
    "duration": 1.168
  },
  {
    "text": "(Laughter)",
    "start": 269.803,
    "duration": 1.671
  },
  {
    "text": "(Applause)",
    "start": 271.498,
    "duration": 1.97
  },
  {
    "text": "Going to America opened doors for me",
    "start": 274.95,
    "duration": 2.938
  },
  {
    "text": "to live up to my full God-given potential.",
    "start": 277.912,
    "duration": 2.89
  },
  {
    "text": "I remember when I arrived,",
    "start": 281.862,
    "duration": 1.529
  },
  {
    "text": "the sponsor family embraced me,",
    "start": 283.415,
    "duration": 1.965
  },
  {
    "text": "and they literally had to teach me\neverything from scratch:",
    "start": 285.404,
    "duration": 3.329
  },
  {
    "text": "this is a microwave,\nthat's a refrigerator --",
    "start": 288.757,
    "duration": 2.748
  },
  {
    "text": "things I'd never seen before.",
    "start": 291.529,
    "duration": 2.709
  },
  {
    "text": "And it was also the first time",
    "start": 294.262,
    "duration": 1.749
  },
  {
    "text": "I got immersed into a new\nand different culture.",
    "start": 296.035,
    "duration": 3.362
  },
  {
    "text": "These strangers showed me",
    "start": 300.159,
    "duration": 3.339
  },
  {
    "text": "true love.",
    "start": 304.381,
    "duration": 1.514
  },
  {
    "text": "These strangers showed me that I mattered,",
    "start": 307.08,
    "duration": 3.702
  },
  {
    "text": "that my dreams mattered.",
    "start": 312.038,
    "duration": 2.387
  },
  {
    "text": "(Applause)",
    "start": 322.165,
    "duration": 4.279
  },
  {
    "text": "Thank you.",
    "start": 328.841,
    "duration": 1.15
  },
  {
    "text": "These individuals had two\nof their own biological children.",
    "start": 332.708,
    "duration": 3.247
  },
  {
    "text": "And when I came in, I had needs.",
    "start": 336.479,
    "duration": 2.768
  },
  {
    "text": "They had to teach me English,",
    "start": 339.691,
    "duration": 2.073
  },
  {
    "text": "teach me literally everything,",
    "start": 341.788,
    "duration": 2.784
  },
  {
    "text": "which resulted in them spending\na lot of time with me.",
    "start": 344.596,
    "duration": 2.727
  },
  {
    "text": "And that created a little bit\nof jealousy with their children.",
    "start": 347.726,
    "duration": 5.434
  },
  {
    "text": "So, if you're a parent in this room,",
    "start": 355.155,
    "duration": 4.509
  },
  {
    "text": "and you have those teenager children",
    "start": 359.688,
    "duration": 3.009
  },
  {
    "text": "who don't want anything to do\nwith your love and affection --",
    "start": 362.721,
    "duration": 4.354
  },
  {
    "text": "in fact, they find it repulsive --",
    "start": 367.099,
    "duration": 1.827
  },
  {
    "text": "I got a solution:",
    "start": 369.701,
    "duration": 1.553
  },
  {
    "text": "adopt a child.",
    "start": 371.278,
    "duration": 1.372
  },
  {
    "text": "(Laughter)",
    "start": 372.674,
    "duration": 1.012
  },
  {
    "text": "It will solve the problem.",
    "start": 373.71,
    "duration": 1.24
  },
  {
    "text": "(Applause)",
    "start": 374.974,
    "duration": 2.131
  },
  {
    "text": "I went on to acquire\ntwo engineering degrees",
    "start": 379.274,
    "duration": 2.63
  },
  {
    "text": "from one of the best\ninstitutions in the world.",
    "start": 381.928,
    "duration": 2.47
  },
  {
    "text": "I've got to tell you:",
    "start": 385.173,
    "duration": 1.265
  },
  {
    "text": "talent is universal,",
    "start": 386.462,
    "duration": 1.817
  },
  {
    "text": "but opportunities are not.",
    "start": 388.303,
    "duration": 2.162
  },
  {
    "text": "And I credit this",
    "start": 391.738,
    "duration": 1.421
  },
  {
    "text": "to the individuals\nwho embrace multiculturalism,",
    "start": 394.296,
    "duration": 3.548
  },
  {
    "text": "love, empathy",
    "start": 398.747,
    "duration": 1.809
  },
  {
    "text": "and compassion for others.",
    "start": 400.58,
    "duration": 1.955
  },
  {
    "text": "We live in a world filled with hate:",
    "start": 404.572,
    "duration": 3.002
  },
  {
    "text": "building walls,",
    "start": 407.598,
    "duration": 1.598
  },
  {
    "text": "Brexit,",
    "start": 409.22,
    "duration": 1.294
  },
  {
    "text": "xenophobia here on the African continent.",
    "start": 410.538,
    "duration": 3.479
  },
  {
    "text": "Multiculturalism can be an answer",
    "start": 415.326,
    "duration": 2.4
  },
  {
    "text": "to many of these worst human qualities.",
    "start": 417.75,
    "duration": 3.626
  },
  {
    "text": "Today, I challenge you",
    "start": 423.308,
    "duration": 2.788
  },
  {
    "text": "to help a young child\nexperience multiculturalism.",
    "start": 426.12,
    "duration": 3.914
  },
  {
    "text": "I guarantee you\nthat will enrich their life,",
    "start": 431.165,
    "duration": 4.083
  },
  {
    "text": "and in turn,",
    "start": 435.272,
    "duration": 1.643
  },
  {
    "text": "it will enrich yours.",
    "start": 436.939,
    "duration": 1.378
  },
  {
    "text": "And as a bonus,",
    "start": 439.519,
    "duration": 1.664
  },
  {
    "text": "one of them may even give a TED Talk.",
    "start": 441.207,
    "duration": 2.013
  },
  {
    "text": "(Laughter)",
    "start": 443.244,
    "duration": 1.483
  },
  {
    "text": "(Applause)",
    "start": 445.269,
    "duration": 2.365
  },
  {
    "text": "We may not be able to solve the bigotry\nand the racism of this world today,",
    "start": 450.218,
    "duration": 4.922
  },
  {
    "text": "but certainly we can raise children",
    "start": 455.164,
    "duration": 3.704
  },
  {
    "text": "to create a positive,\ninclusive, connected world",
    "start": 459.772,
    "duration": 3.498
  },
  {
    "text": "full of empathy,",
    "start": 463.81,
    "duration": 1.577
  },
  {
    "text": "love",
    "start": 466.29,
    "duration": 1.278
  },
  {
    "text": "and compassion.",
    "start": 467.592,
    "duration": 1.29
  },
  {
    "text": "Love wins.",
    "start": 469.361,
    "duration": 1.172
  },
  {
    "text": "Thank you.",
    "start": 470.557,
    "duration": 1.15
  },
  {
    "text": "(Applause)",
    "start": 471.731,
    "duration": 3.039
  }
]